The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the traveling salesperson problem in regular graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are all likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses techniques from graph theory and combinatorics, which are also relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
